Pre-Game Insights: Experts favored Finland to win based on their current form.
Markku Kanerva led Finland to Euro 2020 and has since kept them afloat in the Nations League's second tier.
Finland suffered a major setback at the start of their third straight League B campaign, losing 3-0 in Greece while producing just one shot on target.
Finland has not won any of their first five meetings with Ireland, but have since won back-to-back games against them.
Ireland have failed to win any of their first five meetings with Finland, but have since lost both games by a 1-0 scoreline.
Ireland's new manager, Heimir Hallgrimsson, faces the challenge of avoiding consecutive losses for the first time in charge.
Ireland's recent poor form includes conceding twice in a 2-0 reverse against Greece and losing to England in Dublin.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Finland has not won any of their last five away games and will be relieved to be back on home soil.
Ireland have not scored in 12 of their 18 Nations League matches and have gone winless through all eight away games.
